                <div id="versionCompareContent" class="WPC-editableContent">
                  <span class="diffAdd"></span><font size="2">The Raid point system helps the clan leaders know who participated in raids, who&#39;s been actively attending raids and who is elegible to get items from the clan storage.<br />
                  <br />
                  <font size="2"><b>So, what&#39;s this so called &quot;point system&quot;?</b></font><br />
                  <br />
                  Is basically a homemade exp chart for clan mates, created by the clan leader. See the next example to understand what&#39;s being explained.</font><br />
                  <br />
                  <div align="center">
                    <div align="left">
                      <div align="center">
                        <b><font color="#FF0000">Diablo = <font color="#000000">2</font></font> | <font color="#0000FF">Gerero = <font color="#000000">3</font></font> <font color="#000000"></font>| <font color="#FF0000"><font color="#FFA500">Hell Breaker</font> <font color="#FFA500">=</font> <font color="#000000">4</font></font> <font color="#000000"></font>| <font color="#0000FF"><font color="#808080">Vergo =</font> <font color="#000000">5</font><br />
                        <br /></font></b>
                        <div align="left">
                          <font color="#000000" size="2">As you can see each raid boss is given a specified amount of &quot;points&quot;, the clan leader will give points to the players that attended the raid after the Raid boss is killed. The points can be writen in the &quot;Rank&quot; of the player inside the clan member list (alt + y) so only the officials (vices) or the leader can add or take away points.<br />
                          <br />
                          The points are not money, you can&#39;t buy weapons from the clan leader with these points. These are just a reference to let the clan leader know if you&#39;ve been in raids. Clan leaders can change this rule, and make these points into clan money so you can get items from the storage of the clan (but that happens only if the leader says so).<br />
                          <br />
                          <font size="2"><b><br />
                          Ok, now that the system is in my clan; how do I know when to give items?</b></font><br /></font>
                          <ul>
                            <li><font color="#000000" size="2">Simple, you ask your members what items do they need; and you make a list.</font></li>
                          </ul>
                          <ul>
                            <li><font color="#000000" size="2">Once you have the item in storage and you see that only that member needs it and he has a decent amount of raid points, you give it to him.</font></li>
                            <li><font color="#000000" size="2">If 2 or more players need that same item, then you check their raid points and give the item to the one that has the highest points.</font></li>
                            <li><font color="#000000" size="2">If no one asks for items that were gained by doing raids, then the leader should keep them in storage until someone need them.</font></li>
                            <li><font color="#000000" size="2">If 2 players need the same item and they both have the same amount of points, then they should &quot;firework&quot; until one of them gets the highest number or just decide on their own to see who will take the item.</font></li>
                          </ul><font color="#000000" size="2"><b><br />
                          Why give the items in storage for free to my members?</b><br />
                          Well, the members are the ones that killed the boss, without them the items would&#39;ve never been droped. So technically the raid items are not items for the leader, but for the clan members themselves.<br />
                          <br />
                          <b>What is this &quot;clan storage&quot; you keep mentioning?</b><br />
                          In every clan, there should be 1 member that will be considered a storage account (usually a leader will make an alternate account for this). This member will keep in storage every item that was gained in raids. The reason why there should be 1 alt account being storage, is so the leader of the clan don&#39;t get confused with his items and the items of the clan.<br />
                          <br />
                          <br /></font>
                          <div align="center">
                            <font color="#000000" size="2"><font color="#FF0000">Note that this is just 1 method of giving out the loot after raids. There are many more<br />
                            <br /></font></font>
                            <div align="left">
                              <b><font color="#000000" size="2"><font color="#FF0000"><span class="diffAdd">Other Raid point methods:</span><br /></font></font></b>
                              <ol>
                                <li><span class="diffAdd">The Raid items Bids</span></li>
                              </ol>
                            </div>
                            <div align="left">
                              <br />
                            </div>
                          </div>
